From 6ceb33e6889e5077598e250befa79f6ad15f0c9f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RoboticsYY <RoboticsYY@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 21:41:18 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] fix(agenticros): make camera snapshot work end-to-end in
 OpenClaw web UI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fixes "what does the robot see" on OpenClaw gateway 2026.5.31 so the tool is
callable, the full-resolution image reaches the vision model, the model
describes the scene, and the image does not bloat conversation history.

- openclaw.plugin.json: declare contracts.tools (required by 2026.5.31 before
  registerTool() accepts any tool) and set activation.onStartup so the
  before_agent_start context hook registers into the global hook runner.
- ros-camera/snapshot.ts: decode by actual message structure (raw Image vs
  CompressedImage), not the requested message_type, so a wrong hint no longer
  produces garbage bytes mislabeled image/jpeg → fixes OVMS "Image parsing failed".
- tools/ros2-camera.ts: use the topic's real ROS type from discovery to override
  a wrong explicit message_type hint, with a fallback capture on the alternate type.
- context/robot-context.ts: strengthen camera guidance so the model always
  describes what is visible rather than only attaching the image.
- history/strip-camera-image.ts (new): tool_result_persist hook that removes the
  heavy base64 image from the persisted transcript after the capturing turn's
  model call has consumed it — keeps history small and avoids the
  "[chat.history omitted: message too large]" placeholder, with no downscaling.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
